IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: LIST OF EXHIBITS CyberTip 170969775 NARRATIVE On 8/17/2023 the Maryland State Police Internet Crimes Against Children (ICAC) task force received CyberTips: 170969775 from the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC). The CyberTip, which was reported by a concerned citizen, was generated by the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children (NCMEC) due to the citizen reporting on 8/16/2023 at 05:12:00 UTC a user on Snapchat distributed child pornography. The citizenprovided the following information: CITIZEN/COMPLAINANT Sean Simpson Phone: (301) 707-7545 Contact: Yes Email: ironmanfanscs@gmail.com IP Address: 137.103.151.119 Received by NCMEC on 08-16-2023 18:59:46 UTC SUSPECT Relationship to Reporter: Schoolmate Name: Trinity Grapes Approximate Age: 14 Screen/User Name: tgrapes2022 CHILD VICTIM Relationship to Reporter: Schoolmate Name: Natalie Cummings Approximate Age: 14 Screen/User Name: ncumming39 On 8/21/2023 TFC Mueller contacted the Complainant and learned the following: -The Complainant (Sean), suspect and victim(s) all attended Braddock Middle School together -Sean mentioned there was another girls images who were leaked- Carmen Linibergh -3 photos of each girl fully nude -Approximately 10 people in the Snapchat group chat -Sean sent the images to/informed Natalie of the images and then deleted all images -No images were provided to NCMEC On 9/11/2023 TFC Mueller authored a subpoena, for tgrapes2022 and ncumming39 subscriber information, and submitted it to the Howard County States Attorneys Office for endorsement. Case Open, investigation ongoing.
LIST OF EXHIBITS Snapchat Subpoena NARRATIVE On 9/18/2023 TFC Mueller received the Snapchat Subpoena. On 9/18/2023 TFC Mueller submitted the subpoena to Snapchat. Case Open, investigation ongoing.

Heid, of the Maryland State Police Child Recovery Unit, responded to Braddock Middle School, to see if the school was aware of the incident and could potentially provide more information. Investigators met with Assisstant Principle Moriah Cohen, who informed investigators the victim, Natalie Cummins, took numerous nude images of herself when she was in the 6th grade, and the same images have been circulated across school(s) for several years. Mrs. Cohen continued to say, Natalies family is aware of the situations and the schools recommendation was to no longer involve Natalie due to their belief this incident would have a strictly negative impact on Natalie. Investigators were able to identify Trinity Grapes (Address: 830 Manns Terrace, Cumberland, MD, Mother: Krystal Thompson 301-268-6587 Father: Jared Grapes 240-609-9330). Investigators contacted Jared Grapes and informed him of the ongoing investigation, who was very cooperative with law enforcement, stating he would be happy to handle the matter within the family. Case Closed, by excpetion.
